The paper deals with the design of truthful mechanisms in multi-parameter domains, specifically in the context of sponsored search auctions. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) or Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of allocation rules and the focus on social welfare also suggest that the paper could belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the use of algorithms and the design of a new allocation rule suggest that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
